name: Bao Express
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'If you looking for the correct style of food. Sorry, it is not. Fancy enough but nothing related to the food.

Their service was super quick, my dishes were delivered within 5 minutes after my order. All the food were cold when they arrivd my table.

Not tasty enough. The bun meat was dry and small portion, which a qualified meat bun shoul be meaty with juice. This style Chinese food should serve in hot and not pre cook.

At last, I am questioning about how the meat bun was made. You can saw that the bamboo steamer was dry compared to the Siumai one. The Siumai steamer was wet that mean at least the Siumai was steamed in it. Anyway, it was only my observation but mean nothing.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I loved this place! In two weeks took the following: Chinese spring rolls (they were ok), Xiao Long Bao Shangai classic (the filling is very good and the dough is thick and fluffy), Char Siu Bao (basically the big dumplings, they are super tasty, I preferred these to the smaller ones), Aubergines Hong Shao (for sure the best thing we ate, they were delicious, I sincerely recommend these) and finally the Poulet Sweet & Sour (very good as well). We were very hungry and in the end we were quite full. Plus, the service was super kind and welcoming.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very very overrated, you can find better asian
restaurants in Paris. Never order the lemonade, it is just water. The mango sago is a mango lassi with very few tapioca perles and some small chunks of mango. Aubergines and noodles are ok.
Service was great. A shame that food wasn‚Äôt as good. Everything is deeply fried.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved this great place. üòã
Great food, options even for vegans.
Big place so you can be spontaneous, friendly staff.
Enjoy', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This has to be one of THE HIDDEN GEMS of Paris. This isn‚Äôt on any tourist lists of places to eat and it‚Äôs not typical French food, but it is delicious and the vibe in this place is immaculate. We enjoyed it so much, we went back on our last night in Paris to have it again!  Beef Ho Fun is easily the best dish we had in Paris and the Sweet and Sour Chicken is unlike any version we‚Äôve had in the best way possible. Also, if you‚Äôre a dessert person, the lava French toast is a must try!  We would eat here again and again and will recommend this place to anyone traveling to Paris!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: JJAN
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'The food was very good, very close to authentic and the price for a Korean restaurant in Paris was quite ‚Äúaffordable‚Äù. The portions are big so it fills you well. It is a very popular restaurant so it gets crowded (even waiting lines outside) and there isn‚Äôt much space between tables. The staff is really nice and accommodating, if you need anything just ask and they will bring you.
Definitely recommend!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good Korean dishes‚Äîtwo pages of choices. Love my spicy tofu soup. They need more vegetarian choices. The bibimbap bowl should be much hotter as the rice was room temperature so it made the dish less exciting.  Spartan furniture.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Newly opened. Very tasty in a nicely designed restaurant.

Food wise : we got the dish to share. Cheese + chicken, some KFC as well.
It‚Äôs all good. Loved the fried chicken with their honey soy sauce.
Of course, they‚Äôll let you take everything in takeaway if you don‚Äôt finish.

Service wise : they just opened, when it‚Äôs full it gets a bit slow but I‚Äôm sure they‚Äôll improve very soon.

Price wise : I found it very affordable for that kind of Korean cuisine, especially considering it‚Äôs located in the very center of Paris.

I do recommend it.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great prices and great location. Small menu. We got the KFC and Budae Jigae- KFC was great and crispy and juicy. Budae came with two rice and we added spice so that was great. Nice sauce and was not too bad, 7/10. Service was quick.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food looks delicious but is somehow tasteless.
The kimchi pancake is extra oily.
The service was nice and friendly.
Overall atmosphere is loud and fun, good for an affordable dinner with friends if you are in the area and don‚Äôt care much for the food quality.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Flam&go
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "Very quant little Cafe. The decor is amazing. I had a gluten free soup that was lovely. They don't have a vegetarian option but they did have gluten free soup which was tasty... The green tea was lovely.
Wonderful atmosphere, very cozy and away from the rush in the stores..

The staff are young girls not very personable, so don't expect much from them but the place and food itself is lovely and definitely worth trying.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Nice place away from all the people. You have to order at the counter. As it was sunny, we enjoy our break outside. Too bad they had no espresso but the cakes were very good', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Cute little cafe to grab a quick bite‚Ä¶friendly people, beautiful views and great food‚Ä¶we had the svele and sognalapskaus‚Ä¶amazing!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Beautiful place, very cozy, wonderful views, and good bathroom. For a coffee place, it only has filtered coffee and no hot milk, and it wasn't very good. The cakes looked tasty but expensive. However, it has a wide range of dining dishes we didn't try.
Good peaceful place to hide from the rain, but coffee could be better.", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Warm and cozy Kafe in middle of Fl√•m. It was the perfect ending to our trip to Fl√•m. We ordered some coffee, it was luke warm and when we asked for a hot coffee, the Kafe team was very friendly and served us hot coffee promptly and as a warm gesture we were offered chocholate cakes to make up for the coffee üòä', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: BOOM BOOM VILLETTE
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'This review is for Street Banh Mi at the Food Market. Follow a very good review of Vietnamese community group on Facebook, I gave it a try to support my homeland foods and restaurant owners. I tried their special ‚ÄúB√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o‚Äù which is kind of double price of a normal b√°nh m√¨ 8,5‚Ç¨. And that‚Äôs already expensive compared to many good banh m√¨ that I have tried in Paris. It was very noisy there and we needed to wait a bit long. And the ‚ÄúB√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o‚Äù is too far from the b√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o that I know. Dry, no sauce and quantity is not up to the price 15‚Ç¨. The quality is average. And the bread is under baked, white, too soft not crunchy. I usually don‚Äôt spend time to write negative review. I did this time because it isn‚Äôt correct to serve average quality for high price.\nIt deserves 2,5 stars.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A very well conceptualised food court with lots of of options. They have bars,burgers,Asian and Indian food. You can visit it before or after a movie as pathe gaumont is on the same building.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We came here to treat the kids to a morning of fun amidst a busy week of visits in Paris, lured by the prospect of lots of entertainment for them and a nice lunch in the food court. But when we got there, everything but the food court and the cinema was closed - apparently the kids activies won‚Äôt open before a couple of weeks. You would think that‚Äôs something worth mentioning on their website before having people trek all the way to La Villette for nothing! Yet another soulless place where the emphasis is making money. Such a let down.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Kind of expensive for the small size of the portions and low quality of the food. It's just pre-made industrial food reheated in a fancy microwave priced like a normal restaurant. Not worth it.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This review is for Pokke restaurant at Boom Boom villette. Very slow service and they mixed up with our order and gave it to another person. Waited 30 minutes for one bowl.', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Maison Louvard
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "The crookie stole the show during my recent visit. This trendy fusion of croissant and cookie proved to be a flavorful delight, though a bit pricey for its size. While I didn't explore beyond this famed treat, the bakery's array of tempting options suggests it's a spot worth revisiting for those with a sweet tooth üòã", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We called in for lunch and we were greeted by a very friendly waitress. We found the atmosphere to be excellent and very welcoming. Our waitress was very friendly and the food and service were superb. Braised beef cheek with seasonal vegetables and a terrine for starters were simply excellent. The wine was delicious too.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I tried the cookie croissant here few days ago. And it tastes as good as a regular croissant but 5 times more expensive, 7 times if you decide to take a table . Worth the hype? Not really.', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'ü§© crookie whaaaaat! I‚Äôve never had a cookie croissant ü•ê until today and I don‚Äôt think I can ever go back! Absolutely delicious, great cafe very vibrant and busy with lovely decor, perfect place to grab a morning coffee and treat!  As it‚Äôs quite popular service can be a bit slow but still well worth the visit', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I saw this bakery on Social Media and was curious to know why people were given such a high rate to this place. I wanted to check it by myself üòâ The place is cozy and well decorated. The staff is super friendly and the 'viennoiserie' tasteful. The expresso is also really good and compared to other places in the capital, your getting a decent amount of coffee in your cup (not only a few drops). It was good, but wouldn't given them a 5 star rate (even if the bakker has apparently received an award recently). Guess I will have to go a second time (at lunch) to confirm my thoughts... A place to recommend anyhow.", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Best brunch in Paris

I had the Eiffel tour en plat and the blue dragon as a drink

Highly recommend \U0001f90d', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Owner very Nice. New spot in Paris 16th facing the Eiffel tower. Cosy n warm place. Good To come with friends and better To book your table. The dishes are yummy, tasty...', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Going there for a hooka is good enough, but i do not recommend this place for the restaurant.
The food does not match with the pictures you can see online/Instagram. The avocado salad was not sliced but smashed, the multicoloured tomato salad with burrata was cold (from the fridge) and done with regular red tomatoes. The main course's portions are pretty small and not tasty for the price requested.

I was also pretty intrigued when i asked for a jug of water and the waitress told me they do not serve this kind of drink, which implies that i have to buy a bottle of water when I know its not legal to refuse tap water in restaurants in France.

I might come back for a hooka but certainly never for the restaurant.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'One of the best places I‚Äôve ever been in paris. name: RAMEN WANG
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "This is the most delicious ramen I have ever tasted in Paris. It reminds me of the ramen in Tokyo that I missed so much. Fast service, polite staff. Clean and comfortable. There may be a line outside, but it's worth the wait. I'm glad I found this place", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing place! Very good food and good service and fair prices. Every Tuesday they have vegan ramen. Would definitely come back', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I‚Äôve had ramen in Hong Kong and Tokyo and this is definitely one of my favourites of all time. We‚Äôve been several times, at different times of the day and days of the week yet the food has been amazingly consistent every single time.

The pork is their speciality and spectacular, every bite makes me so happy. The soup is always flavoursome and balanced.

Unfortunately they don‚Äôt take booking in advance so you have to queue. One time we went with our friends (~about 8 of us in total) after our wedding and we had to wait a long time as there was a lot of us but as the food was so tasty, people forgot about the long wait.

All of the staff are friendly, wonderful and attentive and it‚Äôs always a pleasure to come here.

While it‚Äôs growing in popularity, I hope it‚Äôll stay consistent and continue to be a gem in the 14th arrondissement.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved to eat with you. Just needed to wait some minutes outside. But was worth it!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Everything was delicious! Ramen was amazing with lots of flavors. The veggie gyozas as appetizers were tasty too. Nice variety of desserts and I really recommend the matcha financiers with ginger ice cream. Nice wine by the glass as well. Very cozy venue and ambience. A must!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: KINGKONG
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We tried a few dishes. Considering everything was prepared very quickly. Fried chicken wings were spicy buy had a very nice sweet glaze, super crunchy. Tteokbokki had interesting flavors, tasted like tajin but with extra spice. Bibimbap was good, but the sauce was very mild.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This restaurant is quite well hidden in a small street near metro station Strasbourg Saint-Denis. By the look of the exterior I probably wouldn‚Äôt have entered had I not checked Google reviews before‚Ä¶ as the decor was somber and didn‚Äôt give an appetizing look to be honest.

However the food proved me wrong, we ordered lunch menu with the fried chicken as starter and bibimbap as main dish. The fried chicken was divine! So juicy and not greasy at all, the sweet and slightly spicy sauce blended perfectly with the batter, very delicious! The bibimbap itself was great too, it contained lots of ingredients especially vegetables, as they continued to cook in the stone ball they created a nice texture and taste together with the rice. I ordered the squid one, I should maybe have taken the beef and porc version as the squid was a bit chewy and not a lot of flavor. The other small negative point was probably that they were not very generous with the the pickled side dishes (see photo).

Overall I had a good dining experience and will definitely go back to try other dishes.

Update: we went back for the fried chicken and rice sticks, super delicious and you wouldn‚Äôt tell they were deep fried! Loved them.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really good place that serve authentic korean dishes!

Definitely a must take: the korean fried chicken, it was crispy and juicy.

Loved the kimchi fried rice with sea food, I would love to have some seaweed on it to be 100% matching with that I got in Korea!

Moreover great beer selection!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great place for late night eating or drinking, korean cuisine is not only about the bbq, kingkong is more like street style korean food with a nice atmosphere, kpop music and great customer service. The man (the owner maybe) was super friendly. Army stew was flavourful and very filling. I didn‚Äôt like the fried chicken very much, properly because of the sauce. The soft tofu stew (sundubu) is also average. All in all, great restaurant to try out and also their menu changes from time to time so it‚Äôs worth a comeback', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Unfortunately, they stopped serving their corndogs, but the food was delicious all the same! A nice Korean restaurant near Sentier, with a cool upstairs ambiance. Recommended!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Trantranzai
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Loved the decor & environment of the restaurant! At the time we arrived (around 6:30pm) the grilled dumplings weren‚Äôt available unfortunately so we took the shrimp steamed ones. It was good but I think it would‚Äôve been better grilled. In terms of noodles with soup, the portions are so big you are easily fulfilled ! Taste is good overall but the noodles were a bit dry even if it was in the soup. I would recommend though in terms of price/quantity/quality ratio it‚Äôs a win', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': '- Location is easy to access, walking distance to Metro & Bus stations.
- Nice service. It was quite busy at dinner.
- Noodles are excellent. The beef noodles are very tasty. The only point is that they serve with quite big amount.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I love this atmosphere and design!!! It's not so often to see these decoration in China nowadays, but really have the feeling of walk into a film or go back to the last century. Food quality is top, i would recommend rice noodle.
. Service is perfect. Thank you and would come back again!!!", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Incredible Szechuan style noodles with authentic flavors. Will definitely be visiting again.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "When you step into this Chinese restaurant in Paris, it's as if you've been instantly transported to China. It's a culinary journey worth experiencing.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Keopi
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Went there early and got a table. One can scan the QR code to see the menu with pictures. Great service and friendly staff. Definitely good place for brunch.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Delicious Korean brunch place! üá∞üá∑\U0001faf6üèº
We had to wait just a little bit for a table inside. It‚Äôs located in a little alley, easy to find if using Google maps.

Small menu but with lots of options!
We got the fried chicken, which tasted just perfect! Very soft on the inside and the seasonings was on point.
Salmon toast and salmon waffle which were both delicious.
The orange juice was very fresh and sweet.
Service was super fast! Friendly staff.
And most importantly, everything is HALAL!
(Expect for one thing which is the ‚Äúspam‚Äù)
Would definitely come back very soon!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'After watching their instagram account, I wanted to come here and try the brunch. It is an ‚Äúinstagramable‚Äù place, and as such, very popular so you‚Äôll have to wait. However, the waiting times are less than expected and it is worth it. The food is great and innovative. I had the waffle with fried chicken and it was delicious and abundant. The fried chicken is perfect and the sauce (sweet and spice) too, although it is not spicy.
The only problem was the time they took to bring our beverages. We ordered the homemade lemonade and we were almost finishing the dish when they brought it. We noticed the service of beverages is slow, so be patient.
In any case, I‚Äôd love to come back to try the sweet options.

üòãüåéüçΩÔ∏è‚úàÔ∏è
Sabor Kairos', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for brunch at 11:30 on a Sunday and waited for half an hour to be seated cause it was quite crowded. It was worth the wait though cause the staff were nice, service was alright and the food was delicious. We had waffles and they placed a bottle of maple syrup on every table.  I had rose tea and my friends had matcha flavoured drinks and they were all good. Reservations are not possible so avoiding peak times would be a good idea.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The location is simply great, not too far from the Grevin museum ! You really get to feel the parisian vibe.
The price was reasonable for a brunch + it was really delicious. The staff is also really nice and attentive.
We went for a kimchi and avocado salmon toast (which if you like salty and spicy kimchi is a perfect match with avocado and salmon). The Rose Latte was too die for with its hint of rose taste. The spicy chicken was really soft (a perfect boneless chicken if I dare say).
And for the dessert the waffle with matcha cream ! The cream paired perfectly with the fruits and the waffle ~ Beware though, the plate is kind of big so if you don‚Äôt have a big appetite it is best to share it.

All in all the pricing, the amount of food and the taste was more than worthy, a 10/10 for me.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

reviews:

name: Land & monkeys
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Absolutely delightful dining experience. Visited here as a birthday treat and was blown away by the food. 8 course tasting meal with an extra little sweet treat at the end. The staff were very friendly and helpful and I thoroughly enjoyed each course, nothing I didn‚Äôt enjoy. Each course was explained by the waiter and it was also very interesting to learn that they produce very minimal waste here as they use every little bit in some way whether added into a sauce or used as a glaze. I‚Äôve been vegan for 2 years and vegetarian for many many years and this is honestly some of the best food I‚Äôve ever eaten. Will definitely visit again. I also thought ¬£55 for the meal was more than reasonable for the quality of food. Nice little touch to have a birthday card for me on the table too.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was creative and tasted fantastic. Everything was vegan too. Every course brought to our table was more delicious than the previous one. The staff were friendly and thoroughly explained each dish brought to our table. The interior of the restaurant was clean and had a nice vibe. I highly recommend this place for a date night or celebration. I‚Äôm not sure if they have earned any Michelin Stars, but they deserve one if not!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Flavoursome dining experience and attentive/kind staff. We really enjoyed our evening here, the food from start to finish was spectacular with interesting flavours and immaculate presentation! We ended up spending 2.5 hours in the restaurant, leaving with a huge smile on our face‚Ä¶ worth the ¬£.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was great and very good value for money and wine pairing really worked so no complaints on that front and well worth a visit. However please put a curtain around the entrance so you don‚Äôt get hit with an icy blast every time the door is opened . It‚Äôs simply and everywhere in Europe . Second and most disappointing please don‚Äôt rush me out the door when I‚Äôm having my digestive. I‚Äôve enjoyed a good meal I‚Äôm relaxing and I want to end my meal comfortably. This was not just us but everyone was rushed out to make way for the second siting . Adjust your course timings don‚Äôt simply say sorry we have our next sitting coming. And finally 2  to 3 tables too many in this small restaurant making it a little more cramped and less personal than I would have liked . Still a great meal though.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'What an excellent experience! We had the 8 course dining experience and it was just phenomenal. We‚Äôve been vegan for 8 years now and have never eaten such imaginative, creative and delicious food before. Would highly recommend to all so you can experience the extensive range of what can be done with just plants!! Our minds were left blown.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

reviews:
